ir Terminal|Yakima]]\n<!-- -->\n| [[FedEx Express]] | [[La Grande/Union County Airport|La Grande]], [[Lewiston\u2013Nez Perce County Airport|Lewiston]], [[Memphis International Airport|Memphis]], [[Grant County International Airport|Moses Lake]], [[Eastern Oregon Regional Airport|Pendleton]], [[Tri-Cities Airport (Washington)|Tri-Cities (WA)]], [[Pangborn Memorial Airport|Wenatchee]], [[Yakima Air Terminal|Yakima]]\n<!-- -->\n| [[UPS Airlines]] | [[Dallas/Fort Worth International Airport|Dallas/Fort Worth]], [[Des Moines International Airport|Des Moines]], [[Louisville International Airport|Louisville]], [[Ontario International Airport|Ontario]], [[Portland International Airport|Portland (OR)]], [[Boeing Field|Seattle\u2013Boeing]], [[Vancouver International Airport|Vancouver]]\n<!-- -->\n| Western Air Express | [[Boise Air Terminal|Boise]], [[Portland International Airport|Portland (OR)]]\n<!-- -->\n}}\n\n==Statistics==\n\n===Top destinations===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size: 96%\"\n|+ '''Busiest domestic routes from GEG<br />(February 2018 - January 2019)'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.transtats.bts.gov/airports.asp?pn=1&Airport=GEG&Airport_Name=Spokane,|title=RITA - BTS - Transtats|publisher=[[Bureau of Transportation Statistics]]|accessdate=1 May 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! Rank\n! City\n! Passengers \n! Carriers\n|-\n|1\n| [[Seattle\u2013Tacoma International Airport|Seattle/Tacoma, Washington]]\n| 572,430\n| Alaska, Delta\n|-\n|2\n| [[Denver International Airport|Denver, Colorado]]\n| 223,030\n| Southwest, United\n|-\n|3\n| [[Portland International Airport|Portland, Oregon]]\n| 159,240\n| Alaska\n|-\n|4\n| [[Salt Lake City International Airport|Salt Lake City, Utah]]\n| 140,520\n| Delta\n|-\n|5\n| [[Phoenix Sky Harbor International Airport|Phoenix\u2013Sky Harbor, Arizona]]\n| 133,260\n| American, Southwest\n|-\n|6\n| [[Minneapolis\u2013Saint Paul International Airport|Minneapolis/St. Paul, Minnesota]]\n| 114,400\n| Delta\n|-\n|7\n| [[McCarran In