{"title_page": "Homestead Records", "text_new": "{{See also|Homestead Records (1920s)}}\n{{use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox record label\n| name        = Homestead Records\n| image       = Homestead Records Logo.png\n| parent      = Dutch East India Trading\n| founded     = {{start date and age|1983}}\n| founder     = [[Sam Berger]]\n| defunct     = {{end date|1996}}\n| distributor = Dutch East India Trading\n| genre       = [[Alternative rock]], [[punk rock]], [[experimental music|experimental]]\n| country     = United States\n| location    = [[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]], U.S.\n}}\n\n'''Homestead Records''' was a [[Long Island]], [[New York (state)|New York]]-based [[record label|sublabel]] of music distributor Dutch East India Trading that operated from 1983 to 1996. The label was known for not paying its artists and not spending any money on promotion.<ref name=magnet/>\n\n==History==\nThe label was created by Barry Tenenbaum. Tenenbaum started a mail-order business, called Lord Sitar Records, from his bedroom when he was a teenager, importing records by [[the Beatles]] and other artists from England that he could sell for a profit in the States.  Tenenbaum had established an extensive distribution network, called Dutch East India Trading, so when the [[Copyright Act of 1976]] curtailed his ability to import artists who already has U.S. labels, he began licensing records for release and he created the Homestead Records imprint for this purpose.  Sam Berger, who worked for Dutch East, became the new labels first manager.<ref name=magnet/>\n\nSam Berger left Homestead the following in 1984 and was replaced by [[Gerard Cosloy]], the creator of the underground art fanzine Conflict. Cosloy would be the sole employee of the label until 1987 when Craig Marks was hired to assist him in running the label. Cosloy and Marks both resigned in 1990. Ken Katkin was the manager from 1990 to 1992, and Steven Joerg from 1992 to 1996.  The label closed in 1996 with its last release being [[Ivo Perelman]]'s ''[[Cama de Terra]]''.<ref name=magnet/><ref name=jarnow/><ref name=jefferies/>\n\n==Artists==\n{{div col|colwidth=10em}}\n* [[Antietam (band)|Antietam]]<ref name=jarnow/>\n* [[Babe the Blue Ox (band)|Babe the Blue Ox]]\n* [[Bastro]]\n* [[Beat Happening]]\n* [[Beat Temptation]]\n* [[Big Black]]\n* [[Big Dipper (band)|Big Dipper]]\n* [[Bloodsport (band)|Bloodsport]]\n* [[Bodeco]]\n* [[Brainiac (band)|Brainiac]]\n* [[Bratmobile]]\n* [[Breaking Circus]]\n* [[Bull (band)|Bull]]\n* [[David S. Ware]]\n* [[Daniel Johnston]]\n* [[Death Of Samantha]]\n* [[Dinosaur Jr]]\n* [[Dredd Foole & the Din]]\n* [[Einst\u00fcrzende Neubauten]]\n* [[Elliott Sharp]]\n* [[Fish & Roses]]\n* [[GG Allin]]\n* [[Giant Sand]]\n* [[Great Plains (Ohio band)|Great Plains]]\n* [[Green River (band)|Green River]]\n* [[Happy Flowers]]\n* [[Honor Role]]\n* [[Ivo Perelman]]\n* [[King Kong (American band)|King Kong]]\n* [[Live Skull]]\n* [[Love Child (band)|Love Child]]\n* [[My Dad Is Dead]]\n* [[Naked Raygun]]\n* [[New Radiant Storm King]] (NRSK)\n* [[Nice Strong Arm]]\n* [[Nick Cave and the Bad Seeds]]\n* [[One Plus Two]]\n* [[OWT (band)|OWT]]\n* [[Phantom Tollbooth (band)|Phantom Tollbooth]]\n* [[Pony (band)|Pony]]\n* [[Salem 66]]\n* [[Screaming Trees]]\n* [[Seam (band)|Seam]]\n* [[Sebadoh]]\n* [[Sleepyhead (band)|Sleepyhead]]\n* [[Smack Dab]]\n* [[Sonic Youth]]\n* [[Sorry (band)|Sorry]]\n* [[Soul-Junk]]\n* [[Squirrel Bait]]\n* [[Stratotanker (band)|Stratotanker]]\n* [[SSD (band)|SSD]]\n* [[Supreme Dicks]]\n* [[Swans (band)|Swans]]\n* [[Table (band)|Table]]\n* [[Tall Dwarfs]]\n* [[The Blackjacks (US band)|The Blackjacks]]<!--[[The Blackjacks (band)]] redirects to [[The Quarrymen]]-->\n* [[The Cakekitchen]]<ref name=jefferies/>\n* [[The Chills]]\n* [[The Dentists]]\n* [[The Dogmatics]]\n* [[The Ex (band)|The Ex]]\n* [[The Flies (band)|The Flies]]\n* [[The Frogs (band)|The Frogs]]\n* [[The Hedonists]]\n* [[The Holy Men]]\n* [[The Mad Scene]]\n* [[The Meatmen]]\n* [[The Membranes]]\n* [[The Micronotz]]\n* [[The Outnumbered]]\n* [[The Pastels]]\n* [[The Proletariat]]\n* [[The Verlaines]]\n* [[Thomas Jefferson Slave Apartments]]\n* [[Trumans Water]]\n* [[Tsunami (band)|Tsunami]]\n* [[U-Men]]\n* [[Uzi (band)|Uzi]]\n* [[Volcano Suns]]\n* [[Weird Paul Petroskey]]\n* [[William Hooker (musician)|William Hooker]]\n* [[William Parker (musician)|William Parker]]\n* [[Wombats (US band)|Wombats]]<!--[[The Wombats]] article is for the UK band-->\n{{div col end}}\n<ref name=magnet/><ref name=discogs/>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of record labels]]\n* [[Matador Records]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n<ref name=magnet>{{cite news\n| first       = Matthew\n| last        = Fritch\n| title       = Homestead Records: Frontier Days\n| date        = 2006-08-25\n| website     = [[Magnet (magazine)]]\n| url         = http://magnetmagazine.com/2006/08/25/homestead-records-frontier-days/\n| accessdate  = 2020-03-01}}</ref>\n<ref name=jarnow>{{cite book\n| first       = Jesse\n| last        = Jarnow\n| title       = Big Day Coming: Yo La Tengo and the Rise of Indie Rock\n| date        = 2012-06-05\n| publisher   = [[Avery Publishing]]\n| isbn        = 978-1592407156\n| url         = https://books.google.com/books?id=oPT5ND18iQ4C&pg=PT105\n| accessdate  = 2020-03-01}}</ref>\n<ref name=jefferies>{{cite book\n| first       = Graeme\n| last        = Jefferies\n| authorlink  = Graeme Jefferies\n| title       = Time Flowing Backwards: A Memoir\n| date        = 2018-12-14\n| publisher   = Mosaic Press\n| isbn        = 978-1771612371\n| url         = https://books.google.com/books?id=UwlpDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT32&lpg=PT32\n| accessdate  = 2020-03-01}}</ref>\n<ref name=discogs>{{Discogs label|label=Homestead Records}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.grunnenrocks.nl/label/h/homestea.htm Label discography]\n\n[[Category:Record labels established in 1983]]\n[[Category:Record labels disestablished in 1996]]\n[[Category:American independent record labels]]\n[[Category:Industrial record labels]]\n[[Category:Post-hardcore record labels]]\n[[Category:Noise music record labels]]\n[[Category:Experimental music record labels]]\n[[Category:Alternative rock record labels]]\n[[Category:Defunct record labels of the United States]]\n", "text_old": "{{See also|Homestead Records (1920s)}}\n{{use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox record label\n| name        = Homestead Records\n| image       = Homestead Records Logo.png\n| parent      = Dutch East India Trading\n| founded     = {{start date and age|1983}}\n| founder     = [[Sam Berger]]\n| defunct     = {{end date|1996}}\n| distributor = Dutch East India Trading\n| genre       = [[Alternative rock]], [[punk rock]], [[experimental music|experimental]]\n| country     = United States\n| location    = [[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]], U.S.\n}}\n\n'''Homestead Records''' was a [[Long Island]], [[New York (state)|New York]]-based [[record label|sublabel]] of music distributor Dutch East India Trading that operated from 1983 to 1996. The label was known to not paying its artists and not spending any money on promotion.<ref name=magnet/>\n\n==History==\nThe label was created by Barry Tenenbaum. Tenenbaum started a mail-order business, called Lord Sitar Records, from his bedroom when he was a teenager, importing records by [[the Beatles]] and other artists from England that he could sell for a profit in the States.  Tenenbaum had established an extensive distribution network, called Dutch East India Trading, so when the [[Copyright Act of 1976]] curtailed his ability to import artists who already has U.S. labels, he began licensing records for release and he created the Homestead Records imprint for this purpose.  Sam Berger, who worked for Dutch East, became the new labels first manager.<ref name=magnet/>\n\nSam Berger left Homestead the following in 1984 and was replaced by [[Gerard Cosloy]], the creator of the underground art fanzine Conflict. Cosloy would be the sole employee of the label until 1987 when Craig Marks was hired to assist him in running the label. Cosloy and Marks both resigned in 1990. Ken Katkin was the manager from 1990 to 1992, and Steven Joerg from 1992 to 1996.  The label closed in 1996 with its last release being [[Ivo Perelman]]'s ''[[Cama de Terra]]''.<ref name=magnet/><ref name=jarnow/><ref name=jefferies/>\n\n==Artists==\n{{div col|colwidth=10em}}\n* [[Antietam (band)|Antietam]]<ref name=jarnow/>\n* [[Babe the Blue Ox (band)|Babe the Blue Ox]]\n* [[Bastro]]\n* [[Beat Happening]]\n* [[Beat Temptation]]\n* [[Big Black]]\n* [[Big Dipper (band)|Big Dipper]]\n* [[Bloodsport (band)|Bloodsport]]\n* [[Bodeco]]\n* [[Brainiac (band)|Brainiac]]\n* [[Bratmobile]]\n* [[Breaking Circus]]\n* [[Bull (band)|Bull]]\n* [[David S. Ware]]\n* [[Daniel Johnston]]\n* [[Death Of Samantha]]\n* [[Dinosaur Jr]]\n* [[Dredd Foole & the Din]]\n* [[Einst\u00fcrzende Neubauten]]\n* [[Elliott Sharp]]\n* [[Fish & Roses]]\n* [[GG Allin]]\n* [[Giant Sand]]\n* [[Great Plains (Ohio band)|Great Plains]]\n* [[Green River (band)|Green River]]\n* [[Happy Flowers]]\n* [[Honor Role]]\n* [[Ivo Perelman]]\n* [[King Kong (American band)|King Kong]]\n* [[Live Skull]]\n* [[Love Child (band)|Love Child]]\n* [[My Dad Is Dead]]\n* [[Naked Raygun]]\n* [[New Radiant Storm King]] (NRSK)\n* [[Nice Strong Arm]]\n* [[Nick Cave and the Bad Seeds]]\n* [[One Plus Two]]\n* [[OWT (band)|OWT]]\n* [[Phantom Tollbooth (band)|Phantom Tollbooth]]\n* [[Pony (band)|Pony]]\n* [[Salem 66]]\n* [[Screaming Trees]]\n* [[Seam (band)|Seam]]\n* [[Sebadoh]]\n* [[Sleepyhead (band)|Sleepyhead]]\n* [[Smack Dab]]\n* [[Sonic Youth]]\n* [[Sorry (band)|Sorry]]\n* [[Soul-Junk]]\n* [[Squirrel Bait]]\n* [[Stratotanker (band)|Stratotanker]]\n* [[SSD (band)|SSD]]\n* [[Supreme Dicks]]\n* [[Swans (band)|Swans]]\n* [[Table (band)|Table]]\n* [[Tall Dwarfs]]\n* [[The Blackjacks (US band)|The Blackjacks]]<!--[[The Blackjacks (band)]] redirects to [[The Quarrymen]]-->\n* [[The Cakekitchen]]<ref name=jefferies/>\n* [[The Chills]]\n* [[The Dentists]]\n* [[The Dogmatics]]\n* [[The Ex (band)|The Ex]]\n* [[The Flies (band)|The Flies]]\n* [[The Frogs (band)|The Frogs]]\n* [[The Hedonists]]\n* [[The Holy Men]]\n* [[The Mad Scene]]\n* [[The Meatmen]]\n* [[The Membranes]]\n* [[The Micronotz]]\n* [[The Outnumbered]]\n* [[The Pastels]]\n* [[The Proletariat]]\n* [[The Verlaines]]\n* [[Thomas Jefferson Slave Apartments]]\n* [[Trumans Water]]\n* [[Tsunami (band)|Tsunami]]\n* [[U-Men]]\n* [[Uzi (band)|Uzi]]\n* [[Volcano Suns]]\n* [[Weird Paul Petroskey]]\n* [[William Hooker (musician)|William Hooker]]\n* [[William Parker (musician)|William Parker]]\n* [[Wombats (US band)|Wombats]]<!--[[The Wombats]] article is for the UK band-->\n{{div col end}}\n<ref name=magnet/><ref name=discogs/>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of record labels]]\n* [[Matador Records]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n<ref name=magnet>{{cite news\n| first       = Matthew\n| last        = Fritch\n| title       = Homestead Records: Frontier Days\n| date        = 2006-08-25\n| website     = [[Magnet (magazine)]]\n| url         = http://magnetmagazine.com/2006/08/25/homestead-records-frontier-days/\n| accessdate  = 2020-03-01}}</ref>\n<ref name=jarnow>{{cite book\n| first       = Jesse\n| last        = Jarnow\n| title       = Big Day Coming: Yo La Tengo and the Rise of Indie Rock\n| date        = 2012-06-05\n| publisher   = [[Avery Publishing]]\n| isbn        = 978-1592407156\n| url         = https://books.google.com/books?id=oPT5ND18iQ4C&pg=PT105\n| accessdate  = 2020-03-01}}</ref>\n<ref name=jefferies>{{cite book\n| first       = Graeme\n| last        = Jefferies\n| authorlink  = Graeme Jefferies\n| title       = Time Flowing Backwards: A Memoir\n| date        = 2018-12-14\n| publisher   = Mosaic Press\n| isbn        = 978-1771612371\n| url         = https://books.google.com/books?id=UwlpDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT32&lpg=PT32\n| accessdate  = 2020-03-01}}</ref>\n<ref name=discogs>{{Discogs label|label=