{"title_page": "Sre\u0107ko Lisinac", "text_new": "{{short description|Serbian volleyball player}}\n{{Infobox volleyball biography\n| name           = Sre\u0107ko Lisinac\n| image          = Srecko Lisinac 2014 01.jpg\n| image_size     = 220px\n| caption        = \n| nationality    = {{flagicon|SRB}} [[Serbia|Serbian]]\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|1992|5|17}}\n| birth_place    = [[Kraljevo]], [[Serbia and Montenegro|FR Yugoslavia]]\n| height         = 2.05 m\n| weight         = 79 kg\n| spike          = 370 cm\n| block          = 355 cm\n| position       = Middle blocker\n| currentclub    = {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Trentino Volley]]\n| currentnumber  = 20\n| years          = 2009\u20132012<br>2012\u20132013<br>2013\u20132014<br>2014\u20132018<br>2018\u2013\n| teams          = {{flagicon|SRB}} Ribnica Kraljevo<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[AZS Cz\u0119stochowa]]<br> {{flagicon|GER}} [[Berlin Recycling Volleys]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]<br> {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Trentino Volley|Itas Trentino]]\n| nationalyears  = 2012\u2013\n| nationalteam   = {{flagicon|SRB}} [[Serbia men's national volleyball team|Serbia]]\n| medaltemplates = \n{{MedalCompetition|[[Men's European Volleyball Championship|European Championship]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2019 Men's European Volleyball Championship|2019 Belgium/France/Netherlands/Slovenia]]|}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[2017 Men's European Volleyball Championship|2017 Poland]]|}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[2013 Men's European Volleyball Championship|2013 Denmark/Poland]]|}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Volleyball World League|World League]]}}\n{{Medal|Gold|[[2016 FIVB Volleyball World League|2016 Krak\u00f3w]]|}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[2015 FIVB Volleyball World League|2015 Rio de Janeiro]]|}}\n\n}}\n'''Sre\u0107ko Lisinac''' ({{lang-sr-cyr|\u0421\u0440\u0435\u045b\u043a\u043e \u041b\u0438\u0441\u0438\u043d\u0430\u0446}}) (born 17 May 1992) is a [[Serbia|Serbian]] [[volleyball]] player, a member of [[Serbia men's national volleyball team]] and Italian club [[Trentino Volley|Itas Trentino]], German Champion (2013), Polish Champion ([[2017\u201318 PlusLiga|2018]]).\n\n==Career==\n===Clubs===\nIn the 2013/2014 season, Lisinac won the title of German Champion with [[Berlin Recycling Volleys]]. In 2014, he moved to [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]].<ref>[http://www.skra.pl/aktualnosci-przeglad/item/2335-lisinac-marzylem-o-grze-w-belchatowie ''Lisinac: Marzy\u0142em o grze w Be\u0142chatowie''] \u2013 skra.pl \u2013 11-06-2014</ref> He won a title of Polish Champion 2014 with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]].<ref>[http://www.plusliga.pl/news/id/9079 ''PGE Skra mistrzem Polski''] \u2013 plusliga.pl \u2013 27-04-2014</ref> On October 8, 2014 his team won Polish SuperCup.<ref>[http://www.plusliga.pl/news/id/10021 ''ENEA Super Puchar w pi\u0142ce siatkowej 2014 dla PGE Skry Be\u0142chat\u00f3w''] \u2013 plusliga.pl \u2013 08-10-2014</ref> On February 7, 2016 he played with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w|PGE Skra]] and won the 2016 Polish Cup after beating [[ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale|ZAKSA]] in the final. In April 2016 he was a member of the same team which won a bronze medal in the [[2015\u201316 PlusLiga]] championship.<ref>[http://www.skra.pl/aktualnosci-przeglad/item/3683-brazowa-pge-skra ''Br\u0105zowa PGE Skra!''] \u2013 skra.pl \u2013 26-04-2016</ref> At the end of 2017-2018 season he signed a contract with Italian club [[Trentino Volley]].\n\n===National team===\nHe is a bronze medalist of the [[2013 Men's European Volleyball Championship|European Championship 2013]]. On July 19, 2015 [[Serbia men's national volleyball team|Serbian national team]] with him in squad went to the final of [[2015 FIVB Volleyball World League|World League]], but they lost with [[France men's national volleyball team|United States]] 0\u20133 and achieved silver medal.<ref>[http://worldleague.2015.fivb.com/en/intercontinental-group1/news/france-upset-serbia-to-claim-first-world?id=55058 ''France upset Serbia to claim first World League title''] \u2013 fivb.org \u2013 19-07-2015</ref><ref>[http://worldleague.2015.fivb.com/en/intercontinental-group1/news/france-prevail-over-serbia-to-claim-gold?id=55060 ''France prevail over Serbia to claim gold; USA finish third''] \u2013 fivb.org \u2013 19-07-2015</ref> Lisinac received individual award for the ''Best Middle Blocker'' ex-aequo with [[Maxwell Holt]].<ref>[http://worldleague.2015.fivb.com/en/intercontinental-group1/news/frances-earvin-ngapeth-leads-world-league-dream?id=55059 ''France\u2019s Earvin Ngapeth leads World League Dream Team''] \u2013 fivb.org \u2013 19-07-2015</ref>\n\n==Sporting achievements==\n* '''[[CEV Cup]]'''\n** [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] [[2018\u201319 Men's CEV Cup|2018/2019]] \u2013 with [[Trentino Volley|Itas Trentino]]\n\n* '''[[FIVB Volleyball Men's Club World Championship|FIVB Club World Championship]]'''\n** [[File:Gold medal world centered-2.svg|16px]] [[2018 FIVB Volleyball Men's Club World Championship|Poland 2018]] \u2013 with [[Trentino Volley|Itas Trentino]]\n\n* '''National championships'''\n** '''2013/2014''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] German Championship, with [[Berlin Recycling Volleys]]\n** '''2014/2015''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] Polish SuperCup, with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n** '''2014/2015''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2014\u201315 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n** '''2015/2016''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] [[2015\u201316 Polish Cup of men's volleyball|Polish Cup]], with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n** '''2015/2016''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2015\u201316 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n** '''2016/2017''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2016\u201317 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n** '''2017/2018''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] Polish SuperCup, with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n** '''2017/2018''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2017\u201318 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n** '''2018/2019''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[Italian Volleyball League|Italian Championship]], with [[Trentino Volley|Itas Trentino]]\n\n* '''National team'''\n** '''2010''' [[File:Bronze medal europe.svg|16px]] [[2010 Men's Junior European Volleyball Championship|CEV U21 European Championship]]\n** '''2011''' [[File:Bronze medal world centered-2.svg|16px]] [[2011 FIVB Volleyball Men's U21 World Championship|FIVB U21 World Championship]]\n** '''2013''' [[File:Bronze medal europe.svg|16px]] [[2013 Men's European Volleyball Championship|CEV European Championship]]\n** '''2013''' [[File:Silver medal world centered-2.svg|16px]] [[2013 FIVB Men's U23 Volleyball World Championship|FIVB U23 World Championship]]\n** '''2015''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2015 FIVB Volleyball World League|FIVB World League]]\n** '''2016''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2016 FIVB Volleyball World League|FIVB World League]]\n** '''2017''' [[File:Bronze medal europe.svg|16px]] [[2017 Men's European Volleyball Championship|CEV European Championship]]\n** '''2019''' [[File:Gold medal europe.svg|16px]] [[2019 Men's European Volleyball Championship|CEV European Championship]]\n\n===Individually===\n* '''2015:''' [[2015 FIVB Volleyball World League|FIVB World League]] \u2013 Best Middle Blocker\n* '''2013:''' [[2013 Men's European Volleyball Championship|CEV European Championship]] \u2013 Best Middle Blocker\n* '''2016:''' [[2015\u201316 Polish Cup of men's volleyball|Polish Cup]] \u2013 Best Blocker\n* '''2016:''' [[2016 Memorial of Hubert Jerzy Wagner|Memorial of Hubert Jerzy Wagner]] \u2013 Best Middle Blocker\n* '''2016:''' [[2016 FIVB Volleyball World League|FIVB World League]] \u2013 Best Middle Blocker\n* '''2017:''' [[2017 Men's European Volleyball Championship|CEV European Championship]] \u2013 Best Middle Blocker\n* '''2018:''' [[2017\u201318 Polish Cup of men's volleyball|Polish Cup]] \u2013 Best Blocker\n* '''2019:''' [[2019 Men's European Volleyball Championship|CEV European Championship]] \u2013 Best Middle Blocker\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.fivb.org/EN/volleyball/competitions/WorldLeague/2014/Players.asp?Tourn=WL2013&Team=SRB&No=136362 FIVB player profile]\n* [http://www.plusliga.pl/players/id/666 PlusLiga Player profile]\n* [https://www.legavolley.it/player/LIS-SRE-92 legavolley.it Player profile] \n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{commons}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-ach|aw}}\n{{succession box |\n  | before = {{flagicon|SRB}} [[Marko Podra\u0161\u010danin]]\n  | after = TBD\n  | title = Best Middle Blocker of <br>[[Men's European Volleyball Championship|CEV European Championship]]\n  | years = [[2013 Men's European Volleyball Championship|2013]]<br>[[2017 Men's European Volleyball Championship|2017]]<br><small>ex aequo {{flagicon|GER}} [[Marcus B\u00f6hme]]</small><br>[[2019 Men's European Volleyball Championship|2019]]<br><small>ex aequo {{flagicon|SLO}} [[Jan Kozamernik]]</small>\n|}}\n{{succession box |\n  | before = {{flagicon|USA}} [[David Lee (volleyball)|David Lee]]<br>{{flagicon|BRA}} [[Lucas Saatkamp]]\n  | after = {{flagicon|FRA}} [[K\u00e9vin Le Roux]]<br>{{flagicon|CAN}} [[Graham Vigrass]]\n  | title = Best Middle Blocker of <br>[[FIVB Volleyball World League|FIVB World League]]\n  | years = [[2015 FIVB Volleyball World League|2015]]<br /><small>ex aequo {{flagicon|USA}} [[Maxwell Holt]]</small><br/>[[2016 FIVB Volleyball World League|2016]]<br><small>ex aequo {{flagicon|BRA}} [[Maur\u00edcio Souza]]</small>\n|}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lisinac, Srecko}}\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Kraljevo]]\n[[Category:Serbian men's volleyball players]]\n[[Category:Serbian expatriates in Germany]]\n[[Category:Expatriate volleyball players in Germany]]\n[[Category:German Champions of men's volleyball]]\n[[Category:Serbian expatriates in Poland]]\n[[Category:Expatriate volleyball players in Poland]]\n[[Category:Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w players]]\n[[Category:AZS Cz\u0119stochowa players]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Serbian volleyball player}}\n{{Infobox volleyball biography\n| name           = Sre\u0107ko Lisinac\n| image          = Srecko Lisinac 2014 01.jpg\n| image_size     = 220px\n| caption        = \n| nationality    = {{flagicon|SRB}} [[Serbia|Serbian]]\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|1992|5|17}}\n| birth_place    = [[Kraljevo]], [[Serbia and Montenegro|FR Yugoslavia]]\n| height         = 2.05 m\n| weight         = 79 kg\n| spike          = 370 cm\n| block          = 355 cm\n| position       = Middle blocker\n| currentclub    = {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Trentino Volley]]\n| currentnumber  = 20\n| years          = 2009\u20132012<br>2012\u20132013<br>2013\u20132014<br>2014\u20132018<br>2018\u2013\n| teams          = {{flagicon|SRB}} Ribnica Kraljevo<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[AZS Cz\u0119stochowa]]<br> {{flagicon|GER}} [[Berlin Recycling Volleys]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]<br> {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Trentino Volley|Itas Trentino]]\n| nationalyears  = 2012\u2013\n| nationalteam   = {{flagicon|SRB}} [[Serbia men's national volleyball team|Serbia]]\n| medaltemplates = \n{{MedalCompetition|[[Men's European Volleyball Championship|European Championship]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2019 Men's European Volleyball Championship|2019 Belgium/France/Netherlands/Slovenia]]|}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[2017 Men's European Volleyball Championship|2017 Poland]]|}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[2013 Men's European Volleyball Championship|2013 Denmark/Poland]]|}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Volleyball World League|World League]]}}\n{{Medal|Gold|[[2016 FIVB Volleyball World League|2016 Krak\u00f3w]]|}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[2015 FIVB Volleyball World League|2015 Rio de Janeiro]]|}}\n\n}}\n'''Sre\u0107ko Lisinac''' ({{lang-sr-cyr|\u0421\u0440\u0435\u045b\u043a\u043e \u041b\u0438\u0441\u0438\u043d\u0430\u0446}}) (born 17 May 1992) is a [[Serbia|Serbian]] [[volleyball]] player, a member of [[Serbia men's national volleyball team]] and Italian club [[Trentino Volley|Itas Trentino]], German Champion (2013), Polish Champion ([[2017\u201318 PlusLiga|2018]]).\n\n==Career==\n===Clubs===\nIn the 2013/2014 season, Lisinac won the title of German Champion with [[Berlin Recycling Volleys]]. In 2014, he moved to [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]].<ref>[http://www.skra.pl/aktualnosci-przeglad/item/2335-lisinac-marzylem-o-grze-w-belchatowie ''Lisinac: Marzy\u0142em o grze w Be\u0142chatowie''] \u2013 skra.pl \u2013 11-06-2014</ref> He won a title of Polish Champion 2014 with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]].<ref>[http://www.plusliga.pl/news/id/9079 ''PGE Skra mistrzem Polski''] \u2013 plusliga.pl \u2013 27-04-2014</ref> On October 8, 2014 his team won Polish SuperCup.<ref>[http://www.plusliga.pl/news/id/10021 ''ENEA Super Puchar w pi\u0142ce siatkowej 2014 dla PGE Skry Be\u0142chat\u00f3w''] \u2013 plusliga.pl \u2013 08-10-2014</ref> On February 7, 2016 he played with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w|PGE Skra]] and won the 2016 Polish Cup after beating [[ZAKSA K\u0119dzierzyn-Ko\u017ale|ZAKSA]] in the final. In April 2016 he was a member of the same team which won a bronze medal in the [[2015\u201316 PlusLiga]] championship.<ref>[http://www.skra.pl/aktualnosci-przeglad/item/3683-brazowa-pge-skra ''Br\u0105zowa PGE Skra!''] \u2013 skra.pl \u2013 26-04-2016</ref> At the end of 2017-2018 season he signed a contract with Italian club [[Trentino Volley]].\n\n===National team===\nHe is a bronze medalist of the [[2013 Men's European Volleyball Championship|European Championship 2013]]. On July 19, 2015 [[Serbia men's national volleyball team|Serbian national team]] with him in squad went to the final of [[2015 FIVB Volleyball World League|World League]], but they lost with [[France men's national volleyball team|United States]] 0\u20133 and achieved silver medal.<ref>[http://worldleague.2015.fivb.com/en/intercontinental-group1/news/france-upset-serbia-to-claim-first-world?id=55058 ''France upset Serbia to claim first World League title''] \u2013 fivb.org \u2013 19-07-2015</ref><ref>[http://worldleague.2015.fivb.com/en/intercontinental-group1/news/france-prevail-over-serbia-to-claim-gold?id=55060 ''France prevail over Serbia to claim gold; USA finish third''] \u2013 fivb.org \u2013 19-07-2015</ref> Lisinac received individual award for the ''Best Middle Blocker'' ex-aequo with [[Maxwell Holt]].<ref>[http://worldleague.2015.fivb.com/en/intercontinental-group1/news/frances-earvin-ngapeth-leads-world-league-dream?id=55059 ''France\u2019s Earvin Ngapeth leads World League Dream Team''] \u2013 fivb.org \u2013 19-07-2015</ref>\n\n==Sporting achievements==\n* '''[[CEV Cup]]'''\n** [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] [[2018\u201319 Men's CEV Cup|2018/2019]] \u2013 with [[Trentino Volley|Itas Trentino]]\n\n* '''[[FIVB Volleyball Men's Club World Championship|FIVB Club World Championship]]'''\n** [[File:Gold medal world centered-2.svg|16px]] [[2018 FIVB Volleyball Men's Club World Championship|Poland 2018]] \u2013 with [[Trentino Volley|Itas Trentino]]\n\n* '''National championships'''\n** '''2013/2014''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] German Championship, with [[Berlin Recycling Volleys]]\n** '''2014/2015''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] Polish SuperCup, with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n** '''2014/2015''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2014\u201315 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n** '''2015/2016''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] [[2015\u201316 Polish Cup of men's volleyball|Polish Cup]], with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n** '''2015/2016''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2015\u201316 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n** '''2016/2017''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2016\u201317 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n** '''2017/2018''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] Polish SuperCup, with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n** '''2017/2018''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2017\u201318 PlusLiga|Polish Championship]], with [[PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w]]\n** '''2018/2019''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[Italian Volleyball League|Italian Championship]], with [[Trentino Volley|Itas Trentino]]\n\n* '''National team'''\n** '''2010''' [[File:Bronze medal europe.svg|16px]] [[2010 Men's Junior European Volleyball Championship|CEV U21 European Championship]]\n** '''2011''' [[File:Bronze medal world centered-2.svg|16px]] [[2011 FIVB Volleyball Men's U21 World Championship|FIVB U21 World Championship]]\n** '''2013''' [[File:Bronze medal europe.svg|16px]] [[2013 Men's European Volleyball Championship|CEV European Championship]]\n** '''2013''' [[File:Silver medal world centered-2.svg|16px]] [[2013 FIVB Men's U23 Volleyball World Championship|FIVB U23 World Championship]]\n** '''2015''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2015 FIVB Volleyball World League|FIVB World League]]\n** '''2016''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[2016 FIVB Volleyball World League|FIVB World League]]\n** '''2017''' [[File:Bronze medal europe.svg|16px]] [[2017 Men's European Volleyball Championship|CEV European Championship]]\n** '''2019''' [[File:Gold medal europe.svg|16px]] [[2019 Men's European Volleyball Championship|CEV European Championship]]\n\n===Individually===\n* '''2015:''' [[2015 FIVB Volleyball World League|FIVB World League]] \u2013 Best Middle Blocker\n* '''2013:''' [[2013 Men's European Volleyball Championship|CEV European Championship]] \u2013 Best Middle Blocker\n* '''2016:''' [[2015\u201316 Polish Cup of men's volleyball|Polish Cup]] \u2013 Best Blocker\n* '''2016:''' [[2016 Memorial of Hubert Jerzy Wagner|Memorial of Hubert Jerzy Wagner]] \u2013 Best Middle Blocker\n* '''2016:''' [[2016 FIVB Volleyball World League|FIVB World League]] \u2013 Best Midd